Valoarea emisiilor CO2 conform WLTP: Valoarea emisiilor CO2 conform WLTP, Punctajul V(n) reprezintă punctajul aferent Valoarii emisiilor CO2 conform WLTP
Punctajul pentru factorul de evaluare tehnic „valoarea emisiilor de CO2 conform WLTP” se acorda astfel: 
a) pentru cea mai mică valoare declarată a emisiilor de CO2, oferta va primi 15 puncte; 
b) pentru o valoare mai mare a emisiilor de CO2 decât cea de la punctul a), punctajul se acordă astfel: V(n)= (cea mai mica valoarea emisiilor de CO2/valoarea emisiilor de CO2 declarată) x 15 puncte; 

          Pentru demonstrarea valorii emisiilor de CO2 conform WLTP va fi acceptat orice mijloc de probă adecvat, precum fișă tehnică/un dosar tehnic al producătorului sau un raport de testare de la un organism recunoscut.

criteria_from_actual_contract_translated:
Value of CO2 emissions according to WLTP: The value of CO2 emissions according to WLTP, the score V(n) represents the score corresponding to the value of CO2 emissions according to WLTP.
The score for the technical evaluation factor “value of CO2 emissions according to WLTP” is awarded as follows:
a) for the lowest declared value of CO2 emissions, the bid will receive 15 points;
b) for a higher value of CO2 emissions than the one at point a), the score is awarded as follows: V(n) = (lowest CO2 emissions value / declared CO2 emissions value) x 15 points;

To demonstrate the value of CO2 emissions according to WLTP, any suitable means of proof will be accepted, such as a technical sheet/a technical file of the manufacturer or a test report from a recognized body.

Extended warranty (GE): The extended warranty may not be less than 12 months and greater than 48 months. The scoring is calculated as follows:

a) For the largest extended warranty (GE max) offered, the maximum score allocated to the evaluation factor is awarded, namely 40 points;
b) For any other extended warranty offered compared to that provided at point a), the score is calculated according to the algorithm:

GE = (GEn / GEmax) x 40

Where:
GE is the score obtained by the admissible offer under evaluation;
GEn is the extended warranty of offer n;
GEmax is the maximum extended warranty offered among the admissible offers.

Delivery term (TL): The delivery term may not be greater than 3 months from the date the contract enters into force, and may not be less than 1 month, as this is considered unrealistic by the Contracting Authority. The scoring is calculated as follows:
a) for the shortest offered Delivery Term (TL min), the maximum score allocated to the evaluation factor is awarded, namely 20 points;
b) for another Delivery Term than that provided at point a), the score is calculated according to the algorithm:
TL = (TL min / TLn) x 20
Where:
TL is the score obtained by the admissible tender under evaluation;
TL min is the shortest offered Delivery Term among the admissible tenders;
TL n is the Delivery Term of tender n.

