Extension of warranty period: The minimum duration of the performance warranty is 3 years. For a warranty duration shorter than the minimum acceptable duration of 3 years, the offer will be declared non-compliant.
The extension of the warranty period is done by adding whole years (e.g.: 3 years + 1 year = 4 years, 3 years + 2 years = 5 years). Calculation algorithm:
The scoring for the extended warranty of the products is granted as follows:
0 (zero) points for the minimum warranty of 3 years;
5 (five) points for extending the warranty period from 3 years to 4 years, i.e., for one extra year of warranty;
10 (ten) points for extending the warranty period from 3 years to 5 years, i.e., for two extra years of warranty;
No intermediate scoring is granted for intervals shorter than 12 months. For offers that allocate a product warranty beyond 5 years, the maximum score of 10 points will be granted.

Warranty granted for the products: The minimum accepted duration is 24 months, and the maximum accepted duration is 60 months. Offers that include a warranty for a period shorter than 24 months will be declared non-compliant and, consequently, will be rejected. Beyond the maximum duration, the offer will not receive additional points. The tenderer shall present within the technical proposal a statement regarding the warranty period for the offered products. A single warranty term will be accepted. Scoring is awarded as follows:
a) For the longest warranty period, the maximum score of 15 points is awarded;
b) For another warranty period than that provided under letter a), but not less than 24 months, the score is awarded as follows: PT(a) = Gof/Gmax × 15, where: Gof = the warranty period of the offer being evaluated (n), expressed in months; Gmax = the longest warranty period, expressed in months. Clarifications: Other time periods (in days/other units of time) than those at points a and b are not accepted for expressing the warranty period and support for products, for which points are awarded.

